# API Test Results for BSF-Nutrifeed Backend

1. Register API
POST /api/register
Request Body: {"name":"John Doe","email":"john@example.com","password":"123456"}
Response: {"msg":"User created"} 201 Created

2. Login API
POST /api/login
Request Body: {"email":"john@example.com","password":"123456"}
Response: {"access_token":"<JWT_TOKEN>"} 200 OK

3. Add Feed
POST /api/feed
Request Body: {"feed_type":"Worm Feed","quantity":5}
Response: {"msg":"Feed added"} 200 OK

4. Get Feed
GET /api/feed
Response: [{"type":"Worm Feed","quantity":5}] 200 OK

5. Monitor API
POST /api/monitor
Request Body: {"larvae_growth":2.5,"input_log":"waste added","output_log":"larvae harvested"}
Response: {"msg":"Monitoring saved"} 200 OK